From ba4949f79cc04afc794c2368d28689c66b181532 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <assistant@local>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 12:56:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(hero): implement LedgerCollapsingHero with scroll-driven
 transformation

What changed:
- New LedgerCollapsingHero: a reusable slot-based collapsing hero surface
  in the design system. Interpolates height, corner radius, and background
  between expanded and compact states. Two composable slots receive
  collapseProgress so callers choreograph their own transitions. Carries
  no business logic or dashboard awareness.
- New LedgerHeroDefaults: single token object holding all hero dimensions
  (ExpandedHeight, CollapsedHeight, CornerRadius, Background). No magic
  numbers inside the composable.
- DashboardScreen rebuilt on Box + LazyColumn + hero overlay pattern.
  Collapse progress derived from LazyListState via derivedStateOf.
  Dashboard-specific content (greeting, balance, progress bar) provided
  through expandedContent/compactContent slots with staggered graphicsLayer
  transitions.
- Dashboard hero thresholds extracted into private HeroTransitions object.
- Snap behavior extracted into private HeroSnap object with an Enabled
  flag. Experimental: disable or remove if it feels artificial.
- KDoc on every new primitive explaining design intent.

Why:
- The static hero card was the root cause of the "collection of cards"
  feel. A scroll-driven collapsing hero is Ledger's signature interaction.
  Making the container reusable means any future screen (accounts, analytics)
  can host its own hero without reimplementing the scroll coordination.

What did not change:
- QuickStatsSection, RecentTransactionsSection, InsightSection untouched.
- LedgerHeroCard.kt retained (not deprecated in this commit).
- GreetingHeader and MonthlySummaryCard retained, no longer imported by
  DashboardScreen.
- No navigation, no Room, no ViewModels, no parsers. Package moves: zero.

How verified:
- No stale imports in DashboardScreen (grep verified: 0 hits).
- Signature matches NavHost call site.
- No design documents included in this patch.
- Patch self-applies on Commit B.
- Compilation is the build's word.

Note:
- graphicsLayer import: uses androidx.compose.ui.graphics.graphicsLayer.
  If build reports unresolved reference, replace with
  androidx.compose.ui.draw.graphicsLayer or let Android Studio resolve.
- All visual proportions are hypotheses. Adjust after device testing.
